## Visual/Themes
- Implement subtle satisfying animations, like the jackpot number scrolling up instead of just statically increasing
- Can utilize popular media (eg. games, TV shows) as the slot machine themes, for example, a Minecraft themed slot machine will have mob as emojis and winnings corresponding to Minecraft achievements/gameplay
  - Runs into the risk of IP rights infringement, especially when using it for monetization purposes like the slot machine, can be addressed by making the slot machine very similar to the theme instead of copying it
- Instantenous wins are boring and less interesting than more drawn out wins, during a big win/jackpot the wheel can spin for a longer duration to increase anticipation and dopamine
- Since most slot interfaces are static and repetitive (especially when not spinning the wheel), secondary animations can be added, like a looped hanging piggy bank animation that swings around
  - The secondary animation can also respond to the current winnings/actions, like the piggy bank jiggling when a near miss/winnings happen, and visually filling up as the jackpot increases

## Gameplay
- Instead of having a single interaction (lever pull), we can add additional interactions, giving them a sense of more control
  - ex: The player can pay more for a respin option after a spin for a single slot
- Include a pity system (should be shown rather than hidden) as a progress bar. Players are mathematically and psychologically more likely to keep playing for a guarenteed win
- Display/broadcast other player's jackpot for all players would create FOMO and cognitive bias
  - There are strict regulations against showing fake winner notifications to manipulate players
